
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And I select 'Yes' radio button from Contrast enhanced box from Page 03
And I select 'Individual' radio button from Sequences box from Page 03
And I select 'DWI' from 'Weighting' dropdown menu from Page 03
And	I go to Page 06 of Thoracic MRT
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Pleural thickening/Mass' from the dropdown menu
And I select 'I describe' or 'I know' radio button

When I select 'Characterization II' tab
Then 'T1w Signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'T2w Signal' slide bar is enabled
And 'Diffusion restriction' checkbox is enabled

And 'Outward' radio button is enabled
And 'Inward' radio button is enabled

And 'Fat' checkbox is enabled
And 'Focal signal voids' checkbox is enabled
And 'Necrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemorrhage' checkbox is enabled
And 'Cystic changes' checkbox is enabled

And 'No' radio button is enabled
And 'Little' radio button is enabled
And 'Significant' radio button is enabled

And 'Nodular configuration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Chest wall infiltration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Extrapleural fat tissue infiltration' checkbox is enabled
And 'Arrosion of adjacent osseous structures' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hemorrhage' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Fat' checkbox
Then 'Macroscopic' checkbox is enabled
And 'Microscopic' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Cystic changes' checkbox
Then 'Simple' radio button is enabled
And 'Complex' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Little' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Entire lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled
And 'In nidus' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Significant' radio button
Then 'Homogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Heterogeneous' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Entire lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'Central' radio button is enabled
And 'Septal' radio button is enabled
And 'In nidus' radio button is enabled
